/**
 * _questionBank.js
 *
 * 497 total questions across all categories and difficulty tiers
 * 
 * Run this to see more details about total questions:
    * npm run qcount
 * 
 *  Run this to see total questions generated by users:
    * curl https://fitefinance.com/api/total-questions -H "x-admin-secret: YOUR_ADMIN_SECRET"
 * 
 * A curated bank of finance interview questions organized by category and difficulty.
 * Used to inject few-shot examples into the question generation prompt so that
 * gpt-4o-mini sees real calibration samples on every request instead of relying
 * on a single hardcoded example.
 *
 * Each entry: { q: string, math: boolean, format: string }
 *   q      — the question text
 *   math   — true if the question requires calculations or quantitative reasoning
 *   format — "scenario" | "pitch" | "walk-through" | "comparison" | "pressure-test"
 *
 * format values:
 *   scenario      — opens with a specific financial situation or company context
 *   pitch         — asks candidate to recommend, argue for, or defend a position
 *   walk-through  — asks candidate to walk through a process or methodology step by step
 *   comparison    — compares two alternatives and asks for trade-off analysis
 *   pressure-test — presents a constraint or edge case and asks what they'd do
 *
 * To add a new category, add a new top-level key matching a value in CATEGORIES.
 * Each category should have Easy, Medium, and Hard arrays.
 * Target: at least 3 questions per format per difficulty tier per category.
 */

